When I denied knowledge of these workers, the call was transferred via WhatsApp to a second individual named Inspector William Wong, claiming to be from the Immigration and Checkpoints Authority. 
He instructed me to transfer money to a bank account to support the investigations. As I was scared, I complied with his requests. As a result, I made the following transaction:
A transaction of $97451.44 was made to CITIBANK account 15396695 on 2025-03-27.
I realized I had been scammed when the individuals became uncontactable. I also verified the situation with the Ministry of Manpower and Immigration and Checkpoints Authority, 
where there were no records of Michael Lee and Inspector William Wong.
"}]

query: I received a suspicious SMS claiming to be from DBS. It was very convincing at first, but I now realize it was a phishing attempt. They wanted me to verify my identity through a link they sent. The link was https://secure-dbs-login.com/verify. They mentioned something about outstanding bills that needed to be paid, which made it sound urgent. The contact number they used was +6591322047. I did provide my card credentials on that fake site,  it was real, because they made it seem so legitimate. I lost $225.90 due to an unauthorized transaction. They asked for my card details like the number and CVV, which I mistakenly provided because the website looked convincing. I don't think they asked for anything else specific besides my card number and CVV. The whole setup looked pretty much like the actual bank website, which is why I didn't suspect anything at the time. I think that's everything I recall.
